1.title: Return of the Jayde-Eye
1.plot: Kendra declares war when she hears rumors of her mother's tell-all book. A new manager and publicist talk of a possible Girls Next Door reunion. Kendra and Jessica head to Sundance to party.

11.plot: Kendra lets LaVance know she and Colin have reconciled. LaVance shares information about Patti. Girls Next Door reunion planning leads to a meeting with former roommate, Bridget Marquardt.

16.plot: Eric's surprise visit forces Colin to decide if he should reunite with his father. Bridget gives Kendra a special gift. Eric offers Kendra advice on where to place her priorities. Kendra sees her music video.

2.plot: Kendra struggles to dive off a 3-meter board for the television show "Splash" but then finds out that she is expected to do a tandem dive off an even higher board.

3.title: The Ex Files
3.plot: Kendra is invited back on "Splash," this time to do a tandem dive with Hank, and finds out that one of her ex-boyfriends is working out at Hank's gym.

4.plot: After Kendra gets in a car accident, her doctor tells her that she may have suffered a stroke.

5.title: Mum Mum's the Word
5.plot: While waiting for the results of her MRI, Kendra visits her mother, brother, and grandmother in San Diego.

6.plot: It's Kendra's 28th Birthday and Hank sets up a trip to Miami for her and her friends. Hank realizes the bootcamp he set up in Turks & Caicos isn't going to happen which causes a rift between him and Travelle.

7.plot: In Miami, Kendra finds out Jessica renewed her marriage vows with friends in Hawaii without her which hurts her feelings. Hank tells her that he canceled Turks & Caicos which leads to a fight.

8.plot: Kendra does her radio show tryout with Pat McAfee. Hank has a movie role that involves putting on a clown wig and acting opposite Bruce Jenner.

9.plot: Kendra does her radio show tryout with Pat McAfee. Hank has a movie role that involves putting on a clown wig and acting opposite Bruce Jenner.

10.plot: Pat McAfee gifts Kendra & Hank a trip to Big Bear for their fourth anniversary. Pat's girlfriend, Kyle, Jessica, Travelle and his girlfriend join them.

11.title: Cabin Fever
11.plot: While partying in Big Bear Hank worries Kendra isn't happy being married. Kendra and Hank are disappointed that Pat isn't as fun as he used to be.

12.plot: Kendra accompanies her friend Jessica to a Playboy photo shoot. As a result of her car accident, Kendra is still afraid to drive. Hank has to drive her everywhere. Kendra and Hank go to a car dealership to look into buying a new car, and Kendra takes a test drive but has to pull over and ask Hank to drive back to the dealership. Kendra reluctantly goes to a therapist to help conquer her fear of driving. She also tells Hank that she wants to remove her IUD so they can have another baby.

13.title: Pulling the Goalie
13.plot: While Hank is away on a guys-only camping trip, Jessica accompanies Kendra to the doctor to have her IUD removed, whether Hank is on board or not!

14.title: High Wired
14.plot: Kendra goes to Vegas to host The World's Biggest Bachelorette Party. After being asked to zipline her entrance, she has a meltdown. Once home, Kendra wants to work through her fears and expand their family.

1.title: Spilled Milk
1.plot: Kendra's marriage is on the rocks, and Jessica commiserates with her; flashbacks show Kendra and Hank in seemingly happier times when she gave birth to their daughter Alijah -- just five weeks earlier.

2.title: Cutting the Cord
2.plot: Kendra takes baby Alijah to the pediatrician and decides to reach out to her mom, from whom she has been estranged for nearly a year.

3.title: Damage Control
3.plot: Fearing that she's going to lose all her endorsements, Kendra meets with her business advisers; Hank returns home and denies having cheated on Kendra, but she doesn't believe him.

4.title: No Beef Patti
4.plot: After not speaking for a year, a visit from Kendra's mom leaves her with more questions than answers in the wake of Hank's alleged sex scandal. Kendra struggles when Hank returns from New Mexico.

5.title: Girls' Night Bout
5.plot: Kendra's girls night out turns ugly when she learns that Jessica is keeping a secret about Hank's alleged tryst, making her question Hank and plunging her deeper into despair.

6.title: Game Over
6.plot: Kendra is a ticking bomb when she learns Hank told Kyle the truth about his alleged affair. Kendra explodes, threatens divorce and kicks Hank out of the house. Someone is sent to Urgent Care.

7.title: The Moment of Truce
7.plot: Kendra is determined to learn why Hank won't confess the truth about his alleged affair. Kendra gets honest and discovers her role in Hank's silence.

8.title: Where's Poppa?
8.plot: With Hank out of the house, Kendra goes back to the Playboy Mansion to visit with her ex-boyfriend Hugh Hefner. His advice about second chances gives Kendra the courage to find her father and get some answers.

11.plot: Kendra's dream of reuniting with her father comes true in Costa Rica.

12.title: Sons of Beaches
12.plot: When Hank brings Little Hank to Costa Rica, Kendra has mixed feelings. She's excited to introduce Little Hank to his grandpa, but worried her marital problems will ruin her long overdue reunion with her dad.

13.plot: After a dream-come-true meeting with her father, Kendra feels complete. But her happiness is quickly crushed when she learns that her mom has been trashing her on social media while she was away.

14.plot: Kendra and Hank have a date night to address their relationship.

1.plot: With the details of Hank's sex scandal now out in the open, Kendra heads to London for work and play. When a racy photo of Kendra and a former footballer hits the press, Hank questions if Kendra's gone too far.

2.title: A London Bridge Too Far
2.plot: Despite Hank's concerns, Kendra continues her wild time in London. After a date with singer Jake Quickenden and a steamy radio interview with host Matt Edmonson, Kendra is warned not to let things go too far.

3.plot: Kendra returns home from her solo trip to the UK, after partying with an NFL player and indulging her wild side. Hank is hurt by her antics, and Kendra admits she still struggles after last year's scandal.

4.title: Catty Shack
4.plot: Kendra questions if traditional married life is right for her. A therapy session leads to a tearful break down when she admits to texting other men after the scandal.

5.title: Family Matters
5.plot: A visit from Hank's parents stirs up emotions in Kendra, making her question married life and her relationship with her mom. Past issues surface when Kendra considers contacting her mom.

6.title: Assistant Living
6.plot: Kendra enlists the help of an old friend when she signs on for a celebrity cooking show in NYC. Away from home, Kendra confides that she and Hank need to move forward, not backwards, or their marriage is over.

7.title: Travails with My Aunt
7.plot: While working in NYC, Kendra meets her long-lost aunt and gets heated about her fall out with her mom. Later that night, Kendra parties with Eddie and poses for some sexy photos at a gay club.

9.title: Payback Is a Holly
9.plot: When Kendra's handed a public trashing in Holly Madison's tell-all book, she's shocked and outraged, and eager to confront her former housemate about her scandalous accusations.

10.title: Close Encounters of the Hank Kind
10.plot: Kendra reaches out to her ex, Hugh Hefner, after Holly's scandalous accusations. In couples therapy, Kendra admits to texting other men and intimacy issues after Hank's sex scandal.

11.title: The Sexorcist
11.plot: Kendra and Hank meet a sex therapist who gives them love energy exercises that prove challenging for the competitive couple. Frustrated, Kendra threatens to walk out.

12.title: Dots Amore
12.plot: Kendra and Hank attend an intimacy retreat as a last resort to strengthen their troubled marriage. When Hank questions Kendra's seriousness during a romantic dinner, the retreat takes a turn for the worse.

13.title: Tantric or Treat
13.plot: Kendra and Hank invite Jessica and Kyle over for dinner to share what they've learned at their sex retreat. Kendra takes over the kitchen and shares some fun intimacy games with her friends.

14.title: Breast Intentions
14.plot: Kendra's dad, Eric, surprises the family with his new fiancee, Amy. Kendra's happy for her dad, but wary of Amy's motives. When things get wild at a Playboy Mansion party, Eric calls Kendra and Hank for help.

15.title: Midsummer's Night Mare
15.plot: After a wild night at the Playboy Mansion, Kendra wonders if her dad's fiancee, Amy, is in the relationship for the wrong reasons. Amy apologizes and Kendra reluctantly gives her another chance.

16.title: Kendra's Time Out
16.plot: Kendra's wild night out with her friends takes a turn for the worse, when late-night clubbing with hot young guys makes Kendra break her promise to Hank, and he's had enough.

17.title: Hankless in Seattle
17.plot: Kendra's late-night partying finally pushes Hank over the edge. Hank gives Kendra an ultimatum and tells her she must decide. Kendra surprises Hank in Seattle to talk about their future.

18.title: Last Rites
18.plot: After Kendra's Seattle trip doesn't go as planned, she heads to her father's wedding in San Diego, but when Hank is nowhere to be found, she's left wondering if her marriage has passed the point of no return.

2.plot: Kendra keeps a secret from Hank. Patti breaks down in tears, upset by Eric's role in Kendra's life and hoping to reunite with Hank. Patti agrees to meet with a book publisher, but doesn't tell Kendra.

3.plot: Hank loses it when he finds out about Patti's tell all book threat. Patti has a secret meeting with a famous book publisher who digs for dirt on Kendra.

4.plot: Kendra shares surprising news with her mom. Patti is shocked when she learns how Hank really feels about her. Patti keeps a secret from Kendra; Colin and Patti are at odds.

5.title: Sex tips and the city
5.plot: Kendra is all nerves at her NYC audition. A sexy and exciting job offer causes trouble for Kendra, when she makes a big decision without Hank. Patti talks tell all and family drama at girls' night.

7.plot: Kendra storms out after giving Patti an ultimatum. Patti is urged to confront Hank. Kendra meets with an acting coach to prep for her sexy, new play. Hank is shocked when Patti shows up unannounced.

8.plot: While Kendra gets revealing news about her role in a sexy Las Vegas play, Patti makes a surprise visit to see Hank. Unable to regain Hank's trust, Patti is forced to choose between fame and family.

11.title: Frenemy Mine
11.plot: Kendra parties in Vegas; Patti storms out. When Kendra confronts Patti, Patti reveals she distrusts Jessica. Colin is shocked by news of Patti's tell-all book.

12.title: Be careful what you wish for
12.plot: Kendra's tested at rehearsals for her sexy Las Vegas play when they flip the script on her. Colin confronts Patti about her tell-all book. Kendra worries about opening night.

13.title: Playdates
13.plot: Kendra fears Patti will ruin her opening night. Patti splurges on an extravagant purchase with the big advance for her tell-all. Kendra spoils her kids in Vegas. Patti & her publisher devise a secret plan.

14.title: Papa don't preach
14.plot: Kendra prepares for the worst as opening night draws near; Patti and Colin worry about an unwanted reunion with Eric and his new wife; Kendra fears her dream to reunite her family could be a big mistake.

15.title: Undressed Rehearsal
15.plot: Kendra's opening night is threatened by drama from the epic, 20-year reunion of Patti, her son, Colin and ex-husband Eric. Jessica confronts Patti about her "fame whore" claims.

16.title: The parent trapped
16.plot: Kendra's Sin City debut spins out of control when mom and dad clash in a shocking family fiasco 20 years in the making. A surprise visitor spills Patti's shocking secret, leaving Kendra fuming.
